{
  "stem": "20978.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] A distinguished rabbi, and then there was the shamas, the [NON-ENGLISH], you know, that was all part of their employees of the shul.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The only one I remember is the cantor, and the-- oh yes, yeah, the [NON-ENGLISH] Gross, the Yiddish name, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because he has a son here that's a chazzan in the Forest Hills Jewish Center, Yeah, his name was Gross.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Typical Shabbos, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Typical Shabbos was, going way back when I was very young, my mother sent us to the mikvah.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We came home, got dressed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Friday night she light candles, and my father and my brother and I went to shul.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the early years, my younger years where we didn't have any hatred from the goyim, it was very pleasant.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Shabbos, we went to shul.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On the way home, we stopped at the bakery, picked up the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The neighborhood smelled from when the baker opened the oven.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "All the children were coming out-- they could smell it all over the neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was so nice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My mother baked challahs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, before you're 13, you-- you carry it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no eruv no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because as a child I remember my cousin was born.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And his bris was on Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had to carry the knife for the the mohel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, these things I remember like it was yesterday.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, of course, they had the kiddush in the house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Shabbos was very nice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Friends come over, and they play.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact we had a little hallway like where I had my own little shul as-- as a child.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I-- I was a very good Jew that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I still am, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
